data.title: Alan Farrell, TD
data.meta_description: Alan Farrell was elected to the 31st Dáil for Dublin North on the 25th February 2011. Prior to his election Alan worked in local Government since 2004.
data.text:
Alan Farrell is the Chairperson of the Fine Gael Parliamentary Party. He is also the Fine Gael Dáil spokesperson on Justice and is the Fine Gael Dáil Party Whip. He is a TD in the 32nd Dáil having previously been elected to the 31st Dáil as representative for Dublin North.

Prior to his election to Dáil Éireann, Alan had been working in local Government since 2004. At age 26 he was one of the youngest members elected to Fingal County Council. He was appointed as Mayor of Fingal in 2007.
